            <title><![CDATA[Everything We Saw At Nintendo's Last Big Direct For The OG Switch And More Of The Week's Top News]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-ubisoft-minecraft-1851773101</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/everything-we-saw-at-nintendos-last-big-direct-for-the-og-switch-and-more-of-the-weeks-top-news.1148718/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-ubisoft-minecraft-1851773101<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="cc4b95e8d90b81970e9bbb750c4a63c2" data-recommend-id="image://cc4b95e8d90b81970e9bbb750c4a63c2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel / Dotemu<!-- -->, <!-- -->Mojang / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft<!-- -->, <!-- -->Island Records / Epic Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="cc4b95e8d90b81970e9bbb750c4a63c2" data-recommend-id="image://cc4b95e8d90b81970e9bbb750c4a63c2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The big event of the week was Thursday’s Nintendo Direct, the last one focused on the original Switch before the curtain gets pulled back on its successor next Tuesday. However, we also have details on some great games that are a steal right now on PSN during Sony’s spring sale, the lowdown on a big structural shakeup at Ubisoft, and info on <em>Minecraft</em>’s big visual upgrade, coming later this year. Read on for these stories and more.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ba27e04561120076a0db160837189243" data-recommend-id="image://ba27e04561120076a0db160837189243" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Samus Aran holds her fist aloft and it seems to glow with some kind of magical purple energy. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Samus Aran holds her fist aloft and it seems to glow with some kind of magical purple energy. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ba27e04561120076a0db160837189243" data-recommend-id="image://ba27e04561120076a0db160837189243" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Samus Aran holds her fist aloft and it seems to glow with some kind of magical purple energy. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>With the era of the original Switch just about to set below gaming’s horizon, Nintendo has hit the internet with a curtain call of a Direct for the portable console. - Claire Jackson <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-march-27-2025-metroid-pokemon-dragon-qu-1851772682&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-march-27-2025-metroid-pokemon-dragon-qu-1851772682">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1a2eba87b80e16867d7643447d1f9e63" data-recommend-id="image://1a2eba87b80e16867d7643447d1f9e63" data-format="jpg" data-width="1914" data-height="1076" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Devil May Cry's Dante walks toward a horror in the sky. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Devil May Cry's Dante walks toward a horror in the sky. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1a2eba87b80e16867d7643447d1f9e63" data-recommend-id="image://1a2eba87b80e16867d7643447d1f9e63" data-format="jpg" data-width="1914" data-height="1076" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Devil May Cry's Dante walks toward a horror in the sky. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Sony is closing March out with its 2025 spring sale across PlayStation 5 and PS4. There are a lot of big games that are a great deal right now, thanks to discounts of up to 90 percent off, including one of my personal favorite games of 2024.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ps5-spring-sale-kingdom-come-resident-evil-cheap-1851772499?_gl=1*1e2dvnr*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzE2ODQ0Ny40My4xLjE3NDMxODE3OTguNjAuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ps5-spring-sale-kingdom-come-resident-evil-cheap-1851772499?_gl=1*1e2dvnr*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzE2ODQ0Ny40My4xLjE3NDMxODE3OTguNjAuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="a85004ef73f16d8eef2391335f240e40" data-recommend-id="image://a85004ef73f16d8eef2391335f240e40" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario Kart 9 is displayed on a Switch 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mario Kart 9 is displayed on a Switch 2. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a85004ef73f16d8eef2391335f240e40" data-recommend-id="image://a85004ef73f16d8eef2391335f240e40" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario Kart 9 is displayed on a Switch 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>With only a week to go until the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-reveal-trailer-date-nintendo-mario-kart-9-1851739487&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-reveal-trailer-date-nintendo-mario-kart-9-1851739487">Switch 2's big Nintendo Direct showcase</a></span>, there’s new reporting about when the console will launch and some of what players can expect from the hardware’s first six months.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-release-date-nintendo-direct-mario-kart-9-1851772264&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-release-date-nintendo-direct-mario-kart-9-1851772264">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="944532dbb80493ae8712e4e064da9bf6" data-recommend-id="image://944532dbb80493ae8712e4e064da9bf6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="944532dbb80493ae8712e4e064da9bf6" data-recommend-id="image://944532dbb80493ae8712e4e064da9bf6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>During today’s Nintendo Direct, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-release-date-april-2025-1851740848&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-release-date-april-2025-1851740848">the last one before the big Switch 2 Direct next month</a></span>, the company shared a big change it’s making to digital games next month. While it will allow you to share digital titles with friends and family members, this is still Nintendo we are talking about, so the whole system is a bit weird and complicated.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-digital-games-virtual-game-cards-vgc-switch-2-1851772706&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-digital-games-virtual-game-cards-vgc-switch-2-1851772706">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9f601fdd325be4d7c6eecae74259c68e" data-recommend-id="image://9f601fdd325be4d7c6eecae74259c68e" data-format="png" data-width="1123" data-height="632" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Art shows various Ubisoft games. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Art shows various Ubisoft games. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9f601fdd325be4d7c6eecae74259c68e" data-recommend-id="image://9f601fdd325be4d7c6eecae74259c68e" data-format="png" data-width="1123" data-height="632" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Art shows various Ubisoft games. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Ubsioft will spin off its most successful game franchises, including <em>Assassin’s Creed</em>, <em>Far Cry</em>, and <em>Rainbow Six Siege</em>, into a separate subsidiary thanks to a $1.25 billion investment from Chinese conglomerate Tencent. The massive deal allows the founding Guillemot family to remain in control of the publisher despite its recent struggles and cratering share price.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ubisoft-tencent-assassins-creed-far-cry-rainbow-six-1851772796&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ubisoft-tencent-assassins-creed-far-cry-rainbow-six-1851772796">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="99f6aac016f4fb6b427d72d845262cc5" data-recommend-id="image://99f6aac016f4fb6b427d72d845262cc5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel / Dotemu</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="99f6aac016f4fb6b427d72d845262cc5" data-recommend-id="image://99f6aac016f4fb6b427d72d845262cc5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/avengers-doomsday-4-cast-announcement-stream-mcu-marvel-1851772474&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/avengers-doomsday-4-cast-announcement-stream-mcu-marvel-1851772474">Marvel</a></span> and Dotemu just announced <em>Marvel Cosmic Invasion, </em>a co-op, ‘90s-inspired beat ‘em up starring famous comic book characters and set to launch later this year. The cool-looking brawler is from the same studio that brought us 2022's very, very good <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/tmnt-shredders-revenge-review-tribute-game-dotemu-multi-1849077972?_gl=1*1hfyg9q*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzA4ODc1Mi4zOS4xLjE3NDMwODkwODcuNTIuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/tmnt-shredders-revenge-review-tribute-game-dotemu-multi-1849077972?_gl=1*1hfyg9q*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzA4ODc1Mi4zOS4xLjE3NDMwODkwODcuNTIuMC4w"><em>TMNT: Shredder’s Revenge</em></a></span><em>.</em> - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-cosmic-invasion-brawler-dotemu-tmnt-co-op-switch-1851772740&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-cosmic-invasion-brawler-dotemu-tmnt-co-op-switch-1851772740">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="701b2a44f910ceac2002512dd52c1db3" data-recommend-id="image://701b2a44f910ceac2002512dd52c1db3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Sabrina Carpenter holding a machete with the Victory Royale graphic in the corner." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Sabrina Carpenter holding a machete with the Victory Royale graphic in the corner." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Island Records / Epic Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="701b2a44f910ceac2002512dd52c1db3" data-recommend-id="image://701b2a44f910ceac2002512dd52c1db3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Sabrina Carpenter holding a machete with the Victory Royale graphic in the corner." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Whenever <em>Fortnite</em> adds a playable character from one of my various hyperfixations, my friends say, “Ken finally has to start playing <em>Fortnite</em>.” Dashing their hopes time and again, Epic has yet to put out a character that has actually compelled me to download its pop culture mash-up battle royale. I may be about to face my greatest test yet, however, because it seems like <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/sabrina-carpenter-may-be-the-next-playable-celebrity-coming-to-fortnite-festival/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/sabrina-carpenter-may-be-the-next-playable-celebrity-coming-to-fortnite-festival/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pop star Sabrina Carpenter is coming to the game</a></span>, and as someone who listened to her smash hit “Espresso” <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/spotify-wrapped-2024-sabrina-carpenter-espresso-streams-1851714545&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/spotify-wrapped-2024-sabrina-carpenter-espresso-streams-1851714545">1500 times last year</a></span>, am I not duty-bound to show up for my queen? - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/fortnite-sabrina-carpenter-icon-skin-leak-festival-1851772197&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/fortnite-sabrina-carpenter-icon-skin-leak-festival-1851772197">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="b0068c8ac194e121a9e1f3b7266bad5c" data-recommend-id="image://b0068c8ac194e121a9e1f3b7266bad5c" data-format="png" data-width="1170" data-height="660" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Players ride a Ghast to a sunset. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Players ride a Ghast to a sunset. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Mojang / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b0068c8ac194e121a9e1f3b7266bad5c" data-recommend-id="image://b0068c8ac194e121a9e1f3b7266bad5c" data-format="png" data-width="1170" data-height="660" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Players ride a Ghast to a sunset. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>2025 is going to be <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/the-unending-appeal-of-minecraft-1795549429?_gl=1*hthy9t*_ga*MTg4NjY0MzM1NS4xNzM5NDU1MDcz*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MjgyMjEwMi4zMS4xLjE3NDI4MjYyMzguNjAuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/the-unending-appeal-of-minecraft-1795549429?_gl=1*hthy9t*_ga*MTg4NjY0MzM1NS4xNzM5NDU1MDcz*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MjgyMjEwMi4zMS4xLjE3NDI4MjYyMzguNjAuMC4w">a neat year for <em>Minecraft</em></a></span>. Not only is the survival crafting game moving to more frequent feature drops, it’s also getting flying mounts and a big boost to its more than  decade-old graphics. Revealed during a special Minecraft Live, Vibrant Visuals will make every pixelated world full of new life and possibilities thanks to the power of better lighting and reflections. - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/minecraft-vibrant-visuals-ghasts-bedrock-edition-1851771891?_gl=1*1lslbh9*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzE2ODQ0Ny40My4xLjE3NDMxODE3OTguNjAuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/minecraft-vibrant-visuals-ghasts-bedrock-edition-1851771891?_gl=1*1lslbh9*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTc0MzE2ODQ0Ny40My4xLjE3NDMxODE3OTguNjAuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d79aee933c8d455936aa4e6da99e4f40" data-recommend-id="image://d79aee933c8d455936aa4e6da99e4f40" data-format="gif" data-width="800" data-height="450" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An animated gif shows Naked Snake switching ammo with an in-game menu option." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An animated gif shows Naked Snake switching ammo with an in-game menu option." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Gif<!-- -->: <!-- -->Konami / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d79aee933c8d455936aa4e6da99e4f40" data-recommend-id="image://d79aee933c8d455936aa4e6da99e4f40" data-format="gif" data-width="800" data-height="450" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An animated gif shows Naked Snake switching ammo with an in-game menu option." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>I’m just gonna level with ya’ll, I didn’t think much of <em>Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater</em> in 2004. But a new look at an improved gameplay feature in the upcoming remake, <em>Metal Gear Solid Delta</em>, might just be enough to convert this jaded fan who’s convinced the series peaked at <em>Sons of Liberty</em>. In a 12-second clip, Naked Snake can be seen swapping his camo from a foresty look to something more suitable for an urban environment in record time. It’s way faster and less cumbersome-looking than the camo-swapping of the original.  - Claire Jackson <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metal-gear-solid-3-snake-eater-camo-feature-new-1851772814&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metal-gear-solid-3-snake-eater-camo-feature-new-1851772814">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
